00:25.607 --> 00:27.474
♪ I want some
burgers and fries ♪

00:27.475 --> 00:28.976
♪ I want some burgers
and fries ♪

00:28.977 --> 00:30.678
Well, there's some right here!

00:30.679 --> 00:32.412
♪ Don't you tell me no lies! ♪

00:32.447 --> 00:34.348
I can't tell if they're helping
or hurting us out there,

00:34.349 --> 00:35.949
but I think hurting.

00:35.950 --> 00:38.285
Got me in here.
You're here every day, Teddy.

00:38.286 --> 00:40.020
True, but today,
it's 'cause of them.

00:40.021 --> 00:41.488
I think they sound good!

00:41.489 --> 00:43.190
It's better than this
stupid hold music.

00:43.191 --> 00:44.758
Oh, hi, Dr. Rinaldi!

00:44.759 --> 00:46.827
No, no, I love your hold music.

00:46.828 --> 00:49.029
Listen, Doc,
the rash is still there.

00:49.030 --> 00:51.966
I did everything you said...
no shaving, no deodorant.

00:51.967 --> 00:52.967
Oh.
Yeah.

00:52.968 --> 00:54.335
But now it's in both armpits.

00:54.369 --> 00:55.202
Eh.
Mm-hmm.

00:55.203 --> 00:57.004
It's red and flaky...

00:57.005 --> 00:59.306
itchy, bumpy.

00:59.307 --> 01:00.808
Sometimes it's oozy.

01:00.809 --> 01:02.509
I look like Jeff Goldblum
in The Fly.

01:02.544 --> 01:04.178
Lin, please stop
describing your rash.

01:04.179 --> 01:06.113
I'm on the phone
with the doctor, Bob!

01:06.114 --> 01:07.815
I know. Everyone knows. Shh!

01:07.816 --> 01:09.516
Sorry, folks.
It's not...

01:09.517 --> 01:11.118
It's not a big deal.
It's not...

01:11.119 --> 01:12.519
I mean, it doesn't get
in the food.

01:12.520 --> 01:14.088
No, no, no, where are you going?

01:14.122 --> 01:15.956
♪ You want some burgers
and fries! ♪

01:15.957 --> 01:17.358
Talking to you, buddy!

01:17.359 --> 01:19.460
Hey, thumbs up!
Yeah! I got a thumbs up!

01:19.461 --> 01:21.128
That's better than a customer!

01:21.129 --> 01:22.630
Cool song, Gene.
Yeah, you guys sound good.

01:22.631 --> 01:24.865
I'm diggin' it.
You happen to be

01:24.899 --> 01:27.034
in the presence
of child straw prodigies.

01:27.035 --> 01:28.635
We're pretty straw-some.

01:28.636 --> 01:30.537
That's awesome, but with straws?
Strawsome?

01:30.538 --> 01:32.373
We borrow from a lot of genres.

01:32.407 --> 01:35.142
Maybe you guys
can use a little wind?

01:37.012 --> 01:39.546
Whoa! You just walk around
with that thing?

01:39.581 --> 01:41.348
We were at orchestra practice.

01:41.349 --> 01:45.352
And, hey, why make it difficult
when you can make it cymbal?

01:45.387 --> 01:47.655
Are we punnin',
or are we jammin'?

01:51.159 --> 01:53.661
Oh! Oh!

01:53.662 --> 01:57.331
Ah! Ooh!

02:01.169 --> 02:03.170
Guys, you know
what this is, right?

02:03.171 --> 02:05.005
Tuesday? Oh, my God,
it's trash day.

02:05.006 --> 02:07.274
No, we're a band.
Finally, it's happening.

02:07.275 --> 02:09.175
Wait. We weren't a band before?

02:09.176 --> 02:13.180
Uh... before we had the "raz,"
but we needed the "matazz."

02:13.181 --> 02:14.915
So... what do you say?

02:14.916 --> 02:16.583
Yeah! Let's do it! Okay.

02:16.584 --> 02:18.552
All right, but I don't carry
my own equipment.

02:18.553 --> 02:20.220
Yeah! That's the spirit!

02:20.255 --> 02:21.755
Okay, thanks, Doc.

02:21.756 --> 02:23.257
Boy, can that lady
talk about rashes.

02:23.258 --> 02:24.725
What did she say?

02:24.726 --> 02:26.427
The rash'll probably
go away on its own,

02:26.428 --> 02:28.362
but I got to wear a tank
top to let it breathe.

02:28.363 --> 02:29.863
It's festering
under there, I guess.

02:29.864 --> 02:31.899
Look at it.
Can you see it? Lin, please!

02:31.900 --> 02:33.367
It's like
my grandma used to say.

02:33.368 --> 02:35.035
Starve a fever, feed a cold

02:35.036 --> 02:37.104
and air out a festering
rash in a tank top.

02:38.606 --> 02:40.107
Whoa, kids.

02:40.141 --> 02:42.343
Outside only
with the loud noise, remember?

02:42.377 --> 02:44.578
Dad, this is the noise
of a band.

02:44.579 --> 02:46.080
Aw, you guys are a band?

02:46.081 --> 02:48.115
That's fun.
What's your band name?

02:48.149 --> 02:49.483
We're called
The Itty Bitty Ditty Committee.

02:49.484 --> 02:50.918
'Cause we have little ditties.

02:50.919 --> 02:52.286
Oh, now I get it.

02:52.320 --> 02:53.787
All right, everyone.

02:53.822 --> 02:55.956
This is the first official
band practice,

02:55.957 --> 02:58.258
slash, band lunch for
The Itty Bitty Ditty Committee.

02:58.259 --> 02:59.727
Yay!

02:59.728 --> 03:01.295
Oh, we were supposed
to bring slash lunch?

03:01.296 --> 03:03.130
I didn't get the slash memo.

03:03.131 --> 03:05.933
Peter, I think you'll like the
changes I made to your recorder.

03:05.934 --> 03:07.501
Oh.
I electrified it.

03:07.502 --> 03:09.103
Give her a toot.

03:12.340 --> 03:13.774
Cool. Let's wail.

03:15.276 --> 03:17.645
♪ Burger and fries,
burger and fries ♪

03:17.646 --> 03:19.246
♪ Uh, uh, uh, uh! ♪

03:19.247 --> 03:20.914
All right, so we got that song.

03:20.915 --> 03:22.282
Is it really a song, though,

03:22.283 --> 03:23.817
if you just say words
over and over?

03:23.852 --> 03:25.986
Hmm. Good point.
I guess most songs are sung.

03:25.987 --> 03:27.621
But here's the thing.

03:27.622 --> 03:29.256
When I sing, people
don't seem to really, uh...

03:29.257 --> 03:30.758
how do I, uh, put it?

03:30.759 --> 03:32.860
Oh, yeah, enjoy it.
Same with these two.

03:32.861 --> 03:34.428
It depends on
your definition of "enjoy."

03:34.429 --> 03:35.829
I just prefer chanting.

03:35.830 --> 03:37.331
Can you guys sing?

03:37.365 --> 03:39.833
Not if I want to live.

03:39.868 --> 03:42.269
If only we knew someone
who could really sing.

03:42.270 --> 03:44.271
I think we do.
Follow me.

03:44.272 --> 03:46.340
♪ Oh, oh, here she comes ♪

03:46.341 --> 03:48.676
♪ Watch out boy,
she'll chew you up ♪

03:48.677 --> 03:50.611
♪ Oh, oh, here she comes ♪

03:50.612 --> 03:52.346
♪ She's a maneater... ♪

03:52.380 --> 03:55.482
Of course, Darryl...
the computer-nerd songbird.

03:55.483 --> 03:57.651
He's like a funky Bill Gates.

03:57.652 --> 03:59.053
♪ The woman is wild, oh... ♪

03:59.054 --> 04:00.454
Wow, he can sing.

04:00.455 --> 04:02.022
And he hardly even fainted.

04:02.057 --> 04:03.691
♪ Oh, oh, here she comes,
she's a man... ♪

04:03.692 --> 04:06.026
Darryl! Aah! Don't do that!

04:06.027 --> 04:08.829
Darryl, ever think about being
the lead singer of a band?

04:08.830 --> 04:10.397
Like, only every day.

04:10.398 --> 04:12.433
Great! You can be
the lead singer of our band.

04:12.467 --> 04:13.901
You guys are a band?

04:13.902 --> 04:15.402
Why don't you see for yourself?

04:17.305 --> 04:19.005
So, yeah, we're a band.

04:19.040 --> 04:22.309
Guys, this is nice, but...
Casio and straws at lunchtime?

04:22.310 --> 04:23.844
This is kind of kids' stuff.

04:23.845 --> 04:25.746
I'm just saying,
if I'm gonna join a band,

04:25.747 --> 04:28.015
it's gonna be a real band,
like Steely Dan.

04:28.016 --> 04:30.017
Darryl, honey, don't wait
around for Steely Dan.

04:30.018 --> 04:31.685
He's not coming for you.

04:31.686 --> 04:33.187
He's not coming for any of us.

04:33.221 --> 04:34.154
It could happen.

04:34.155 --> 04:35.923
Just sing with us.

04:35.924 --> 04:38.859
If you, like, know a song
that goes with these chords.

04:38.860 --> 04:40.427
Fine. One song,
but nothing from Frozen,

04:40.428 --> 04:42.162
'cause I don't want to cry.

04:46.201 --> 04:47.234
♪ Girls, girls... ♪

04:50.372 --> 04:51.872
Hey, Lenny Destefano.

04:51.906 --> 04:53.841
Are you hiding from one
of your many girlfriends?

04:53.842 --> 04:55.342
Yup. Hey, you guys sound good.

04:55.343 --> 04:57.711
Are you a band? Yes! Um...

04:57.746 --> 04:59.913
You guys want to play
my birthday party this Saturday?

04:59.948 --> 05:01.615
GENE, RUDY, PETER & DARRYL:
Yes! Cool.

05:01.616 --> 05:03.417
Not so fast, Lenny.

05:03.451 --> 05:05.586
We have to go over the
particulars. What do you mean?

05:05.587 --> 05:08.088
We want the corner pieces of the
cake, half of the piñata candy

05:08.089 --> 05:09.890
and ownership of the streaming
and performance rights

05:09.891 --> 05:11.425
worldwide in perpetuity.

05:11.426 --> 05:12.860
I'm not having a piñata.
Get a piñata.

05:12.861 --> 05:15.262
Okay. See you guys Saturday.

05:15.297 --> 05:17.197
Oh, my God!
We just booked a gig

05:17.198 --> 05:18.866
at Lenny Destefano's
birthday party!

05:18.867 --> 05:20.434
So, are you in the band, Darryl?

05:20.435 --> 05:22.569
Heck, yeah,
I'm in the band! Yeah!

05:22.604 --> 05:25.973
The Itty Bitty Ditty Committee
just got their first giggy!

05:29.028 --> 05:31.342
You guys,
I blocked out my schedule

05:31.343 --> 05:32.677
every day after school
for band practice.

05:32.711 --> 05:34.612
Every day?
That's a lot of practice.

05:34.613 --> 05:36.180
We don't want
to sound too rehearsed.

05:36.214 --> 05:37.882
Uh, yeah, Gene, we do.

05:37.883 --> 05:39.417
We want to sound really good.

05:39.418 --> 05:41.385
Lenny Destefano's party
is a big gig.

05:41.420 --> 05:44.088
All right, fine, as long as
practice includes snack breaks.

05:44.089 --> 05:46.190
And bathroom breaks
and commercial breaks

05:46.191 --> 05:47.858
where I describe
my favorite commercials.

05:47.893 --> 05:49.627
Hey, Tina.
Hey, Jimmy Jr.

05:49.628 --> 05:51.362
I guess you heard the news about
the Itty Bitty Ditty Committee.

05:51.363 --> 05:52.797
Huh?
I was gonna tell you

05:52.798 --> 05:54.465
that you're standing
in front of my locker.

05:54.466 --> 05:55.866
Oh. Sorry.

05:55.901 --> 05:57.301
What's the Itty Bitty
Ditty Committee?

05:57.302 --> 05:59.136
Is that one of
those improv groups?

05:59.137 --> 06:01.205
My cousin was kidnapped
by one of them.

06:01.239 --> 06:02.974
That's our band name.

06:02.975 --> 06:04.608
We're playing Lenny Destefano's
party on Saturday.

06:04.609 --> 06:06.711
It goes from 5:00
to question mark.

06:06.712 --> 06:08.646
Just kidding. It ends at 7:30.

06:09.614 --> 06:11.582
Two burgers of the day.

06:11.583 --> 06:13.584
I'm wearing this tank top 'cause
the doctor prescribed it for me.

06:13.619 --> 06:15.586
Lin, you don't have
to say that to every customer.

06:15.587 --> 06:17.221
What? I don't want
people to think

06:17.222 --> 06:18.856
I'm trying to look
like a hot potato.

06:18.890 --> 06:20.291
What's going on under there?

06:20.325 --> 06:21.726
It's just a little hair.

06:21.727 --> 06:24.261
I haven't been shaving
my pits. See?

06:24.262 --> 06:25.296
Oh, my God.

06:25.330 --> 06:27.665
Wait. Wha...?
It's just,

06:27.666 --> 06:29.100
there's so much of it.

06:29.101 --> 06:30.501
How long
since you've stopped shaving?

06:30.502 --> 06:32.436
A few days.
It grows in really fast.

06:32.471 --> 06:34.305
It's like animal fur.

06:34.306 --> 06:36.474
It looks like that guy's hair
from Counting Crows. Yes!

06:36.508 --> 06:38.743
Okay, all right,
everyone's having fun.

06:38.744 --> 06:40.645
Say good-bye to Mr. Jones. Aah.

06:40.646 --> 06:43.614
Guys, I wrote
a song for Lenny's party.

06:43.649 --> 06:45.082
Darryl, here are the lyrics.

06:45.083 --> 06:46.450
"His name is Lenny.

06:46.451 --> 06:47.952
"It is not Jenny.

06:47.953 --> 06:50.187
One time he ate a penny,
and he thought nobody saw."

06:50.188 --> 06:51.789
Is that true?
True enough.

06:51.790 --> 06:53.858
I changed the name of
the guy who ate the penny

06:53.859 --> 06:55.760
from "Gene" to "Lenny,"
and it was a nickel.

06:55.761 --> 06:57.461
And two pennies and a tiny rock.

06:57.462 --> 06:58.829
All right, follow my lead.

07:00.599 --> 07:02.433
♪ His name is Lenny... ♪

07:02.434 --> 07:03.834
You know what?

07:03.869 --> 07:05.303
This key isn't working for me.

07:05.304 --> 07:06.704
Can we try it in D or E flat?

07:06.705 --> 07:08.472
No can do.
Why not?

07:08.473 --> 07:09.941
'Cause no know how to do.

07:09.942 --> 07:12.043
I can only play in this key.

07:12.044 --> 07:14.145
And I don't know
which letter that is.

07:14.179 --> 07:15.546
Yeah, that's it.

07:15.547 --> 07:17.682
Here. Let me see. Uh...

07:19.217 --> 07:20.685
♪ His name is Lenny... ♪

07:20.719 --> 07:23.020
Are we playing in the right key?
Oh, yeah.

07:23.055 --> 07:27.358
♪ One time he ate a penny
and he thought nobody saw... ♪

07:27.359 --> 07:28.726
Whoa!
Whoa!

07:28.727 --> 07:30.728
Well, that was a mess!

07:30.729 --> 07:32.530
Let's not do that again!

07:32.531 --> 07:34.031
Ever. Right guys?

07:34.032 --> 07:35.967
Okay, all agreed.

07:37.369 --> 07:38.803
How was band practice, kids?

07:38.837 --> 07:40.237
Good.
Fine.

07:40.238 --> 07:41.872
I thought it was kind of weird.

07:41.873 --> 07:43.641
Right, guys? Didn't you
think it was weird?

07:43.642 --> 07:45.076
You mean when Darryl
played your keyboard?

07:45.077 --> 07:46.477
And you stood there
looking terrified?

07:46.478 --> 07:47.845
Yeah, that was weird.

07:47.879 --> 07:49.513
Darryl played your keyboard?
Why?

07:49.548 --> 07:52.416
You know how when you only know
how to play in one key,

07:52.417 --> 07:54.518
and the other people want
to play in different keys,

07:54.519 --> 07:56.120
and you're, like,
"What's a key?"

07:56.154 --> 07:59.957
Whoa! Mom, your armpit forests
are really filling out.

07:59.992 --> 08:02.994
You can barely see your rash
anymore, or your skin,

08:03.028 --> 08:04.829
or anything behind you.
Dad, are you there?

08:04.863 --> 08:07.398
Yes, Tina, I'm right here...
behind the armpit hair.

08:07.432 --> 08:08.466
Oh. Good.

08:08.500 --> 08:10.568
I love it! We finally have pets.

08:10.569 --> 08:12.203
I'm calling them
"Laverne and Curly."

08:12.237 --> 08:14.639
Too late. I already named them
"Harry and Sally."

08:14.673 --> 08:16.674
Wait. One's a boy?
Obviously.

08:16.675 --> 08:19.510
It's not a boy. It's a man!
No, it's not! I'd know

08:19.511 --> 08:22.179
if one was Billy Crystal.
Everyone leave my pits alone!

08:22.214 --> 08:24.048
That one just got angry
when you got angry.

08:24.082 --> 08:25.283
Enough!

08:25.284 --> 08:26.784
So, Linda's cooking today?

08:26.785 --> 08:29.053
Yeah, she, uh,
thought she'd be more

08:29.087 --> 08:31.422
comfortable back there today.
I'm hiding my pits.

08:31.456 --> 08:32.857
Lin, would it help
if I took off my shirt

08:32.857 --> 08:34.292
in a show of solidarity?

08:34.293 --> 08:35.993
I got some weird stuff
going on under here.

08:36.028 --> 08:37.160
No. Teddy, no.
Maybe.

08:37.195 --> 08:38.796
Surprise!

08:38.797 --> 08:40.331
As in surprise inspection.

08:40.365 --> 08:41.899
Ugh. Hugo.
Hi.

08:41.900 --> 08:44.368
Hi, Ron.
I see you're busy as usual.

08:44.369 --> 08:46.337
Just do what
you got to do, Hugo.

08:46.371 --> 08:49.407
Write me up for disorganized
napkins or whatever.

08:49.441 --> 08:51.208
Oh, count on it, Bob.
I will.

08:51.209 --> 08:52.810
But let's inspect
the kitchen first.

08:53.912 --> 08:54.879
Hello, Hugo.
Hi, Ron.

08:54.880 --> 08:56.547
Hi, Linda.

08:56.548 --> 08:58.549
Linda, something is unusual
about you today.

08:58.550 --> 09:00.184
What is that?

09:00.218 --> 09:02.019
What? Nothing.
It's nothing.

09:02.054 --> 09:03.688
Think fast!
Ah!

09:03.722 --> 09:05.156
Aha!
Aw.

09:05.157 --> 09:06.791
Linda here is in violation

09:06.792 --> 09:09.560
of Health Code Title 21,
Section A, Paragraph eight.

09:09.561 --> 09:11.562
"Excessive body hair
must be covered."

09:11.596 --> 09:13.264
But I need to wear a tank top.

09:13.298 --> 09:14.732
Need to? Why?

09:14.733 --> 09:16.767
Because of this rash...
shida Jones.

09:16.768 --> 09:18.336
Uh, big fan.
Oh, yeah.

09:18.337 --> 09:19.770
She likes tank tops, too.

09:19.771 --> 09:21.872
She does.
She loves them. Uh-huh.

09:21.907 --> 09:23.908
Well, I happen to have
some armpit hairnets with me.

09:23.909 --> 09:25.409
Ron?
Here you go.

09:25.444 --> 09:27.144
Ugh! Are you kidding me?

09:27.145 --> 09:29.413
If you want to avoid a citation,
you'll keep those on.

09:29.414 --> 09:31.515
Come on, Ron.
Let's go down to the walk-in.

09:31.516 --> 09:33.150
Poke the produce,
see what pokes back.

09:33.185 --> 09:35.086
Great. Now I look ridiculous.

09:35.087 --> 09:37.088
No. They look... good?

09:37.089 --> 09:38.990
Yeah, very, uh... Wow.

09:38.991 --> 09:41.459
It looks like I trapped
two hedgehogs under my arms.

09:41.460 --> 09:42.827
It doesn't...
that much.

09:42.828 --> 09:44.261
I love hedgehogs.
I got to go!

09:44.262 --> 09:45.630
Lin, where are you going?

09:45.631 --> 09:47.098
I'm shaving 'em!

09:47.132 --> 09:48.599
Lin, wait.

09:48.600 --> 09:50.001
Teddy, I'll be right back.

09:50.002 --> 09:51.602
I got to go.
Go to her, Bobby!

09:51.603 --> 09:54.438
Lin, don't do this.
I'm doing it, Bob!

09:54.473 --> 09:56.274
I'm taking it all off!

09:56.275 --> 09:58.776
The doctor said if you shave,
you're just gonna make it worse.

09:58.777 --> 10:01.646
I can't believe I'm saying this,
but leave the hair alone.

10:01.647 --> 10:03.481
I hate this rash, Bobby!

10:03.515 --> 10:05.316
It's turning me into a monster!

10:05.317 --> 10:06.851
You're not a monster, Lin.

10:06.852 --> 10:09.353
Your armpits have
monster qualities, but...

10:09.354 --> 10:11.689
Look, we're gonna fix this. How?

10:11.690 --> 10:13.190
First, you got
to give me the razor.

10:13.191 --> 10:14.659
You're gonna do it?

10:14.660 --> 10:17.361
No. I wouldn't... go near that.
Bob!

10:17.362 --> 10:19.196
We'd have
to rent a hedge trimmer,

10:19.197 --> 10:21.165
or hire, like, a lumberjack
or something like that.

10:21.199 --> 10:22.733
Stop it!

10:22.734 --> 10:24.468
Lin, listen, we're gonna
go on the Internet.

10:24.469 --> 10:26.971
Yeah? We're gonna type
in "rash remedies."

10:26.972 --> 10:30.541
Uh-huh. And we're gonna see
some horrible, horrible images.

10:30.542 --> 10:32.209
But we're also
gonna get some help.

10:32.210 --> 10:33.945
I love you so much, Bobby!

10:37.883 --> 10:39.817
Hi. Wait.

10:39.818 --> 10:41.052
Did we have practice
scheduled during lunch today?

10:41.053 --> 10:42.486
Hey...

10:42.521 --> 10:43.854
Gene.

10:43.855 --> 10:46.791
Uh, maybe, uh,
you should sit down.

10:46.825 --> 10:48.559
Oh, good! I got here
just in time for break,

10:48.560 --> 10:49.927
my favorite part of practice.

10:49.928 --> 10:51.329
Who's on whose lap?

10:51.363 --> 10:52.730
Gene, there's...
there's a reason

10:52.731 --> 10:54.598
why we were practicing
without you.

10:54.599 --> 10:57.134
Because you guys need twice
as much practice as me?

10:57.169 --> 11:00.938
No... It's because
we're making some changes,

11:00.939 --> 11:03.240
and, uh, you are, uh...

11:03.241 --> 11:04.909
We thought we should
be in the band,

11:04.910 --> 11:06.644
and you shouldn't be
in the band. Sorry.

11:06.678 --> 11:08.279
What?! I'm out of the band?!

11:08.280 --> 11:10.815
Well, good luck getting
my sisters to play without me!

11:10.849 --> 11:12.249
Oh, yeah. They're out, too.

11:12.250 --> 11:14.218
Yeah. We're sort of evolving
away from straws.

11:14.219 --> 11:17.622
The thing is, Gene, Rudy
and Peter are trained musicians.

11:17.623 --> 11:21.225
And I kind of figured out how
to sing all your keyboard parts.

11:21.259 --> 11:24.595
You can't sing my part and sing
lyrics at the same time!

11:24.630 --> 11:27.298
Gene, he can.
We've seen it and it's so good.

11:27.299 --> 11:30.368
Yeah, I brought in
a looper pedal, so I can just...

11:30.369 --> 11:31.769
♪ Skoop bop boo boo ♪

11:31.770 --> 11:33.404
♪ Skoop bop boo boo ♪

11:33.405 --> 11:34.805
♪ Skoop bop boo boo,
skoop bop boo boo... ♪

11:34.806 --> 11:36.474
♪ I can sing on top
of my voice ♪

11:36.475 --> 11:39.844
♪ That's me,
this is also me... ♪

11:39.878 --> 11:41.946
But this is my band!
I started all of this!

11:41.947 --> 11:43.714
Yeah, and you're, like,
the most fun member.

11:43.715 --> 11:45.549
Yeah.
Yeah. I'm all drama.

11:45.550 --> 11:47.551
But the thing is
you can't actually...

11:47.552 --> 11:49.553
play.
You only know three chords!

11:49.554 --> 11:51.122
But I know them very well!

11:51.123 --> 11:53.124
Well, two of them
I know very well!

11:53.125 --> 11:55.526
The other one I'm just
getting acquainted with!

11:55.560 --> 11:57.228
This is hard for everyone, Gene.

11:57.262 --> 11:58.462
But mostly for me!

11:58.497 --> 11:59.563
Yeah.
True.

11:59.598 --> 12:00.965
Fine!
You know what I'm gonna do?

12:00.966 --> 12:02.600
I'm gonna get
really, really good

12:02.601 --> 12:04.468
in time for Lenny's party!
Lenny's party's

12:04.503 --> 12:06.938
in two days, Gene.
I know that, Darryl!

12:06.939 --> 12:08.839
You guys are gonna be begging me

12:08.840 --> 12:11.876
to listen to you
beg me to come back!

12:11.910 --> 12:13.244
The door's always open, Gene.

12:13.245 --> 12:15.579
Except can you close it
on your way out?

12:15.614 --> 12:17.615
I will slam it!

12:19.952 --> 12:22.253
Stupid safety door
closing thing!

12:25.217 --> 12:27.153
Oh, kicked out of your own band.

12:27.154 --> 12:28.488
They David Lee Roth'd you.

12:28.522 --> 12:30.323
I'm glad we got kicked out.

12:30.324 --> 12:32.825
That was starting to cut into my
not-going-to-band-practice time.

12:32.826 --> 12:35.228
And that time is precious.
I'm okay with it.

12:35.229 --> 12:37.163
Now I can focus
on my solo straw stuff.

12:37.164 --> 12:38.598
Like drinking liquids.

12:38.599 --> 12:40.400
Guys,
we're gonna get back together.

12:40.401 --> 12:42.268
I'm just gonna become the
greatest musician in the world

12:42.269 --> 12:45.405
in the next 48 hours
and that'll be that. Easy.

12:45.406 --> 12:47.006
What are you gonna do, Gene?
Go down to the crossroads,

12:47.007 --> 12:48.541
make a deal with the devil?

12:48.542 --> 12:51.444
Almost. I'm gonna ask
Ms. Merkin to teach me.

12:51.445 --> 12:52.578
The music teacher at school?

12:52.613 --> 12:53.913
The Queen of the Keys?

12:53.914 --> 12:55.715
Yep! I figure
one quick power sesh

12:55.716 --> 12:57.417
should get me ready
for Lenny's party.

12:57.418 --> 12:59.752
Great plan, honey.
I'm ready for the garlic, Bob.

12:59.753 --> 13:01.554
Not to be all Miss
When Is Dinner

13:01.555 --> 13:03.122
but when is dinner?
And what is dinner?

13:03.123 --> 13:05.124
You've been stirring
that stuff forever.

13:05.125 --> 13:07.794
Oh, this isn't dinner. This is a
home remedy for my armpit rash.

13:07.795 --> 13:09.062
We found it online.

13:09.096 --> 13:11.097
What?! It's well past
dinnertime!

13:11.098 --> 13:13.800
Sorry. It's just...
feed your children.

13:13.801 --> 13:15.435
Okay, uh, Bob,
hand me the oatmeal,

13:15.436 --> 13:17.270
the fish oil,
and the buttermilk.

13:17.271 --> 13:20.306
No fair. Why do your armpits
get to eat all the fun stuff?

13:20.307 --> 13:21.941
Oh, it smells really weird.

13:21.942 --> 13:24.277
Hmm. It's not that bad.

13:24.278 --> 13:26.713
I mean, it's a little weird.
Okay, it's really weird.

13:26.714 --> 13:29.048
I'm just gonna try it.
No! Tina! It's my medicine!

13:29.049 --> 13:30.950
Just give Tina whatever
your armpits don't finish.

13:30.951 --> 13:33.553
I'm so hungry!
Bob, order a pizza.

13:33.554 --> 13:35.955
Get one with oatmeal, fish oil,
and buttermilk on it.

13:35.956 --> 13:38.925
 So you want
 to become a skilled musician.

13:38.926 --> 13:41.294
Yes. Well, good news,
all it takes is practice...

13:41.295 --> 13:42.395
No...
...discipline...

13:42.396 --> 13:43.663
No.
...and hard work.

13:43.664 --> 13:45.498
No! Okay. Hearing a lot of no's.

13:45.499 --> 13:48.267
Look, I just want to get good
enough to get back into my band,

13:48.268 --> 13:50.269
get discovered, make
it big, throw it all away,

13:50.270 --> 13:52.672
get it back again, and we'll
see what happens from there.

13:52.673 --> 13:55.575
Okay. Let's open up
the workbook.

13:55.576 --> 13:59.312
Work book? Do you hear
how you sound right now?!

13:59.313 --> 14:00.747
Gene, settle down.
Listen to this.

14:04.151 --> 14:07.353
That's a terrible song.
It's not a song. It's scales.

14:07.354 --> 14:08.688
Gross.
It's not gross.

14:08.689 --> 14:10.657
It's gross.
It's scales. It can't be gross.

14:10.658 --> 14:11.824
It's gross.

14:11.825 --> 14:13.426
It's not gross! It's scales!
Well, I'm just sayin',

14:13.427 --> 14:14.927
it could use drums or somethin'.

14:14.928 --> 14:16.429
What?
Nothing.

14:26.807 --> 14:29.642
Again. Again?!
We've been doing this for hours!

14:29.643 --> 14:31.644
You've been doing
it for 45 seconds.

14:31.645 --> 14:33.813
Aah! I can't take it anymore!

14:33.814 --> 14:36.649
Gene, you don't become
a skilled musician overnight.

14:36.650 --> 14:39.052
But that's exactly
what I have to do!

14:39.053 --> 14:41.721
Lenny Destefano's
birthday party is tomorrow!

14:41.722 --> 14:45.058
You're playing Lenny Destefano's
birthday party? I was.

14:45.059 --> 14:46.559
Why don't you try
and book next year

14:46.560 --> 14:48.995
or the year after
that and practice until then?

14:48.996 --> 14:51.397
And see if you can get me on
as your opening act, would ya?

14:51.398 --> 14:54.233
Who am I kidding?

14:54.234 --> 14:56.336
I'm never gonna be
a skilled musician.

14:56.337 --> 14:58.171
I think I'm just gonna go home.

14:58.172 --> 15:01.307
Would it help if
I played you out? Maybe.

15:01.308 --> 15:03.376
♪ He's a-leavin' little early,
but that's okay ♪

15:03.377 --> 15:05.378
♪ He seems real depressed
and a... ♪ Okay, not helping!

15:05.379 --> 15:06.813
What?
Not helping!

15:06.814 --> 15:09.449
All right. It was
a work in progress.

15:09.483 --> 15:11.484
There's my little Genethoven.

15:11.485 --> 15:14.087
How was your first music lesson?
What'd you learn?

15:14.121 --> 15:16.155
I learned
that I don't have what it takes.

15:16.190 --> 15:17.657
What are you talkin' about?

15:17.658 --> 15:18.858
You've got swagger,

15:18.859 --> 15:20.026
you got flare, you got panache.

15:20.027 --> 15:21.461
What else is there?

15:21.462 --> 15:23.629
I'm not getting back in my band
or any band!

15:23.630 --> 15:26.232
I'm never gonna get
to hear one of my songs used

15:26.233 --> 15:28.668
in a Hyundai Elantra commercial!
Never!

15:28.702 --> 15:30.470
Aw, I'd give you a hug, hon,

15:30.471 --> 15:32.472
but I'd get stinky pit
paste all over your head.

15:32.473 --> 15:34.207
Why do I never get that warning?

15:34.208 --> 15:35.975
Time to reapply.

15:35.976 --> 15:38.177
Ugh! Oh, God,
you released the beast!

15:38.178 --> 15:40.246
It smells fine
if you don't breathe.

15:40.247 --> 15:42.715
We got to move, Lin.
It's gonna stink up the whole place.

15:42.716 --> 15:44.717
All right, we're goin' out
to the alley to reapply.

15:44.718 --> 15:46.786
Tina, Louise,
comfort your brother.

15:46.787 --> 15:48.221
There, there.

15:48.222 --> 15:50.390
I know what'll make
you feel better.

15:50.424 --> 15:51.524
Here comes Ticklin' Tina.

15:51.525 --> 15:53.726
Tickle, tickle, tickle.

15:53.727 --> 15:55.395
I don't need to be a musician.

15:55.396 --> 15:57.797
In fact,
I don't need music at all.

15:57.798 --> 15:59.632
Really? What?
Stop looking at me like that,

15:59.633 --> 16:01.801
keyboard! You know I'm right!

16:01.802 --> 16:03.169
What would you do instead?

16:03.203 --> 16:05.204
Mmm. Maybe I'll be a baker.

16:05.205 --> 16:07.106
Or a candlestick maker.

16:07.107 --> 16:08.975
♪ Maybe I'll be a potter ♪

16:08.976 --> 16:11.311
♪ Or a teacher
like Welcome Back, Kotter ♪

16:11.312 --> 16:13.813
♪ Maybe I'll juggle
or maybe I'll juice ♪

16:13.814 --> 16:16.149
♪ Be a Top Gun
and be friends with Goose ♪

16:16.150 --> 16:18.418
♪ One thing I know for sure ♪

16:18.419 --> 16:21.654
♪ I don't need music ♪

16:21.655 --> 16:24.590
♪ I don't need you anymore ♪

16:24.591 --> 16:27.160
♪ I don't need music ♪

16:27.161 --> 16:28.928
♪ I'm gonna kick you
right out the door ♪

16:28.929 --> 16:30.363
♪ I... ♪

16:30.397 --> 16:31.664
♪ Don't ♪

16:31.665 --> 16:32.832
♪ Need ♪

16:32.833 --> 16:34.033
♪ Music ♪

16:34.068 --> 16:37.136
♪ Anymore! ♪

16:37.137 --> 16:40.940
Aah! Why don't you take the hint
and leave me alone?!

16:40.941 --> 16:43.276
Here! Take this thing
and get rid of it for me!

16:43.277 --> 16:44.777
What are you saying?

16:44.778 --> 16:47.180
I never want to see
or hear from it again.

16:47.181 --> 16:48.681
Burn it.

16:48.682 --> 16:50.516
Gene,
you don't want to do that.

16:50.517 --> 16:53.486
Take it! I have to report
to the Miramar Naval Air Station

16:53.487 --> 16:55.922
in Miramar, California!

16:58.864 --> 17:01.137
Come on out, sweetie.
You been in there all morning.

17:01.138 --> 17:03.139
Gene, come on, we gotta
open up the restaurant.

17:03.140 --> 17:05.175
No, thank you!
I'm fine!

17:05.209 --> 17:06.443
We missed you at breakfast.

17:06.444 --> 17:08.278
We missed
all your funny banana jokes.

17:08.279 --> 17:10.614
That one where you pretend
the banana is your penis.

17:10.615 --> 17:12.615
Eh, don't love that one. Why?

17:12.616 --> 17:15.050
It's a little easy.
Why? What do you mean, "easy"?

17:15.051 --> 17:17.053
He's got other ones.
Like what? Which ones?

17:17.054 --> 17:19.289
He does the banana mustache,
he does Captain Banana...

17:19.290 --> 17:21.625
Oh, yeah. Ooh! I know
what'll get him out.

17:21.626 --> 17:24.060
Who wants to see Mommy's
big hairy pasty pits?

17:24.060 --> 17:25.462
Nah.
Good idea, Lin.

17:25.463 --> 17:26.829
All right, all right.

17:26.830 --> 17:28.098
Nice try from the B-team.

17:28.098 --> 17:29.799
You guys go ahead downstairs.

17:29.834 --> 17:31.601
The A-team will
take it from here.

17:31.602 --> 17:33.203
Gene, we're coming in.

17:33.237 --> 17:34.638
B-team?
All right. We're leaving

17:34.639 --> 17:36.473
but only because we have
to open the restaurant.

17:36.474 --> 17:38.642
And we're not the B team.
No, like in a good way.

17:38.643 --> 17:40.677
Not in a good way.

17:40.678 --> 17:43.446
So, you're, uh,
still done with music, right?

17:43.447 --> 17:45.315
Yes. You haven't
changed your mind?

17:45.349 --> 17:47.484
Nope.
This is what I'm doing now.

17:47.518 --> 17:49.919
Okay. Cool. Oh!
I almost forgot.

17:49.920 --> 17:52.122
What is this?
That's your keyboard.

17:52.123 --> 17:53.723
We burnt it.
Just like you asked.

17:53.758 --> 17:55.825
That's what you wanted, right?

17:55.826 --> 17:57.961
Yes.

18:00.164 --> 18:04.434
♪ Keyboard, my keyboard ♪

18:04.435 --> 18:08.305
♪ Keyboard, my keyboard... ♪

18:08.339 --> 18:12.142
Keyboard!
I don't want you to be dead!

18:12.176 --> 18:14.511
Aha! We knew it!
We knew you still cared!

18:14.512 --> 18:16.513
And that's why we didn't burn
your keyboard.

18:16.514 --> 18:18.281
What? This isn't my keyboard?

18:18.282 --> 18:20.116
No. We burnt Dad's new socks.

18:20.117 --> 18:21.551
Who does he think he is?

18:21.552 --> 18:23.787
If you want to
see your real keyboard,

18:23.788 --> 18:26.189
put on your burger suit,
do something about that hair,

18:26.190 --> 18:28.124
and come with us.

18:28.125 --> 18:30.193
Come on, Gene, let's play
together, like we used to.

18:30.194 --> 18:33.630
You play the keyboard and we'll
play the cups. Like old times.

18:35.633 --> 18:38.969
No. I can't.
I'm not a real musician.

18:38.970 --> 18:41.371
Well, you're definitely
a real something.

18:41.372 --> 18:44.040
Maybe "musician" just isn't
the right word for you.

18:44.041 --> 18:46.543
Maybe you're a...
musishy.

18:46.544 --> 18:48.211
Come on, Gene.
Just one song.

18:48.212 --> 18:50.547
Yeah. And after that,
if you're still done with music,

18:50.548 --> 18:52.048
we'll really burn this sucker.

18:52.049 --> 18:55.018
Uh...

18:55.052 --> 18:57.053
Mmm... uh... Come on.

18:57.054 --> 18:58.488
There we go.

18:59.657 --> 19:01.624
This is going well.
Mmm...

19:01.659 --> 19:03.927
Mmm...

19:03.928 --> 19:07.130
Hmm. Mmm, mmm, mmm.
There you go.

19:07.164 --> 19:08.498
Mmm.

19:16.607 --> 19:18.742
Look! They got Gene to play!

19:18.776 --> 19:20.910
Wow. They really are the A-team.

19:20.945 --> 19:22.512
